&lt;p&gt;
	The Trust takes food safety for patients and customers extremely seriously and is committed to maintaining high standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Two key issues were raised during the inspection which affected the food hygiene rating:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The temperature of two fridges in the restaurant was found to be inadequate. Although these fridges were known to be faulty and were not intended for use, a staff member had mistakenly placed toasties in one of them on the day of inspection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The temperature of the hot cabinet in Costa was found to be below 63&amp;deg;C during a busy lunchtime period. Although temperature records prior to the inspection showed satisfactory readings, the unit was below the required holding temperature at the time of inspection, and time-based controls could not be demonstrated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Prompt and robust action was taken to address these matters and prevent a recurrence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	We were pleased to also receive positive verbal feedback during the inspection.&lt;/p&gt;
